parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause total brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake pressure
brake pedal goes to the floor
inability to stop the vehicle
vibration or noise from the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause the brake pedal to stick or freeze, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Noise from the brake system
brake pedal feels spongy or soft
brake pedal sticks or freezes
inability to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors and pads can cause vibration, noise, and loss of braking performance, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Vibration or noise from the brake system
brake pedal feels spongy or soft
brake pads worn out
brake rotors warped or rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause loss of control or accidents, especially during sudden stops or hard braking.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake pressure
brake pedal goes to the floor
inability to stop the vehicle
vibration or noise from the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause loss of brake pressure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake pressure
brake pedal goes to the floor
inability to stop the vehicle
vibration or noise from the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bracket holding the ABS wiring can cause stress on the wiring, leading to electrical system failures or accidents.
symptoms: None reported
but dealer has repaired the issue multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat recliner can cause the seat back to fall backwards, leading to injuries or accidents, especially during sudden stops or collisions.
symptoms: The seat back falls backwards
the seat recliner slips out of position
the seat back reclines with a loud "pop"
the seat back moves unexpectedly
the seat back fails to stay in place.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Cruise Control Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the cruise control fails to disengage
the vehicle speeds up on its own
the cruise control switches off while driving.
